Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_proto_mode(25.10)                                    set_proto_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_proto_mode  -  Sets the mode for all the prototyping model commands
       as well as other commands, such as place_design and timeDesign

Syntax
       set_proto_mode

       [-reset]

       [-allow_model_with_io {true|false}]

       [-allow_powerdomain_in_flexmodel {true|false}]

       [-create_dir <directoryName>]

       [-create_high_fanout_psPM {true|false}]

       [-create_lib <libraryName>]

       [-create_metal_fill_NDR <double>]

       [-create_metal_fill_nominal <double>]

       [-create_multi_corner_psPM {true|false}]

       [-create_NDR_psPM_model {auto|on|off}]

       [-create_partition_as_flexmodel {true|false}]

       [-create_pipeline_flop {*AB*}]

       [-create_powerdomain_psPM {true|false}]

       [-create_timing_budget {true|false}]

       [-create_no_flex_filler {true|false}]

       [-identify_algorithm {auto|module_based|instgroup_based}]

       [-identify_estimated_flexmodel_number <number>]

       [-identify_exclude_module {<module1><module2> ...}]

       [-identify_exclude_module_and_parent {<module1> <module2> ...}]

       [-identify_exclude_module_tree {<module1><module2> ...}]

       [-identify_honor_objects_hierarchy {<object_list>}]

       [-identify_max_inst <number>]

       [-identify_min_inst <number>]

       [-keep_inst_file_only {true|false}]

       [-keep_instance_defined_in_sdc {true|false}]

       [-keep_slack_improve_NDR {true|false}]

       [-max_report_NDR_net <double>]

       [-route_net_NDR <ruleName>]

       [-timing_net_delay_model        {best_layer_no_detour|best_layer_block-
       age_aware|use_actual_wire}]

       [-timing_ps_per_micron {M <number1>[:M <number2>] <number3> ...}]

       [-verbose]

       Sets  the  mode for all the prototyping model commands as well as other
       commands, such as place_design and timeDesign. The parameters  in  this
       command  having  prefix  as identify are used by the identify_flexmodel
       command and the  ones  with  create  prefix  are  used  with  the  cre-
       ate_proto_model command.

       Use  the  get_proto_mode command to return the current settings for the
       set_proto_mode command.

Parameters
       -allow_model_with_io {true|false}
              Allows modules with I/O to be selected as FlexModel.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -allow_powerdomain_in_flexmodel {true|false}
              Allows modules that contains power domain(s) to be  selected  as
              FlexModel.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -create_dir <directoryName>
              Specifies the directory to save created models.

              Default: proto_model

              Data_type: string

       -create_high_fanout_psPM {true|false}
              Creates high fanout psPM models.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -create_lib <libraryName>
              Specifies the OpenAccess library to save created models.

              Default: proto_model_lib

              Data_type: string

       -create_metal_fill_NDR <double>
              Creates  metal  fill  that is used by create_ps_per_micron_model
              for creating psPM model for nets with non default rules.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float

       -create_metal_fill_nominal <double>
              Creates metal fill that is  used  by  create_ps_per_micron_model
              for creating psPM model for normal nets.

              Default: 0.5

              Data_type: float

       -create_multi_corner_psPM {true|false}
              Create multi corner psPM models.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -create_NDR_psPM_model {auto|on|off}
              Specifies  whether  create_ps_per_micron_model  should  generate
              psPM model for non default rule or not.

              Default: auto

              Data_type: enums={auto on off}

       -create_no_flex_filler {true|false}
              Specifies whether to create  proto  model  without  adding  flex
              filler.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -create_partition_as_flexmodel {true|false}
              Creates partition specified as flexmodel automatically.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -create_pipeline_flop {*AB*}
              Specifies  a  list  of  pipeline flop instance patterns that are
              used in the design. The default value is an empty list.

              Default: " "

              Data_type: string

       -create_powerdomain_psPM {true|false}
              Creates power domain psPM models.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -create_timing_budget {true|false}
              When enabled, it uses Active-Logic Reduction Technology (ART) in
              timing budget mode during flexModel  generation.  The  FlexModel
              creation  uses  the same settings as the deriveTimingBudget com-
              mand to preserve logic paths so that they yield good timing bud-
              gets later on in the flow.

              Note: This option should only be specified if design has  parti-
              tions defined.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -identify_algorithm {auto|module_based|instgroup_based}
              Identifies  the  proto algorithm. Specifying instgroup_based en-
              ables the instance group based identify_proto_model.

              Default: auto

              Data_type: enums={auto module_based instgroup_based},

       -identify_estimated_flexmodel_number <number>
              Specifies the estimated flexModel number to identify the  design
              when using the instance group based identify_proto_model.

              Default: 20

              Data_type: int

       -identify_exclude_module

              {<module1><module2>  ...}"  Excludes the specified module(s) but
              not its sub-modules for being marked as models.

              Default: ""

              Data_type: string

       -identify_exclude_module_and_parent

              {<module1 ><module2> ...}" Excludes the specified module(s)  and
              its parents for being marked as models.

              Default: ""

              Data_type: string

       -identify_exclude_module_tree

              {<module1><module2>  ...}"  Excludes the specified module(s) and
              its sub-modules for being marked as flexModels.

              Default: ""

              Data_type: string

       -identify_honor_objects_hierarchy {<object_list>}
              Specifies the hierarchy of the list of objects that the instance
              group based identify_proto_model will honor.

              Default: ""

              Data_type: string

       -identify_max_inst <number>
              Specifies the maximum instance count threshold of a module to be
              marked as model. The default value is eight percent of the total
              instance count and goes no lower than 300000 instances.

              Default: -1

              Data_type: int

       -identify_min_inst <number>
              Specifies the minimum instance count threshold of a module  that
              is to be marked as a model.

              Default: 1000

              Data_type: int

       -keep_inst_file_only {true|false}
              Specifies  that  the instance list for flexmodels should only be
              kept in the keep_inst_file.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -keep_instance_defined_in_sdc {true|false}
              Specifies that the flexmodel will keep the instance  defined  in
              the sdc file.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -keep_slack_improve_NDR {true|false}
              Specifies  that  report_NDR_WNS_gain will keep top critical nets
              as non default rule nets.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -max_report_NDR_net <double>
              Specifies that create_ps_per_micron_model creates psPM model for
              nets with non default rules.

              Default: 0.05

              Data_type: float

       -route_net_NDR <ruleName>
              Specifies that create_ps_per_micron_model creates psPM model for
              nets with non default rules.

              Default: ""

              Data_type: string

       -timing_net_delay_model {best_layer_no_detour|best_layer_block-
       age_aware|use_actual_wire}]
              Allows you to the set mode of calculating wire delay.

              Note: Using the best_layer_blockage_aware option,  Innovus  uses
              an  obstacle  aware approach for estimating the channel-routing-
              wire-length between two timing  points.  The  timeDesign  -proto
              command is aware of routing blockages and other partition fences
              when the best_layer_blockage_aware option is specified.

              Default: best_layer_no_detour

              Data_type: enums={best_layer_no_detour best_layer_blockage_aware
              use_actual_wire}

       -timing_ps_per_micron {<M<num1>[:M<num2>] psPerMicron ...}, {MetalLay-
       erName1[:MetalLayerName2] psPerMicron ...} {1[:2] psPerMicron ...}, or
       {view {M<num1>[:M<num2>] psPerMicron ...} ...}, {view {MetalLayer-
       Name1[:MetalLayerName2] psPerMicron ...} ...} {view {1[:2] psPerMicron
       ...} ...>}
              Specifies  the estimated delay per micron for each routing layer
              (DB or LEF layer names). You can also specify layer  pair  value
              for each view.

              Data_type: " "

              Data_type: string

       -reset Restores  all  parameters modified using set_proto_mode to their
              default settings. The -reset parameter must be the first parame-
              ter specified. If you specify -reset by itself, the software re-
              sets all set_proto_mode parameters to their default  values.  If
              you  specify  parameters  after -reset, the software resets only
              those parameters to their default values.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -verbose
              Outputs detailed information into the log file.

              Data_type: false

              Data_type: bool

Examples
              * The following command sets the prototyping mode to exclude the
                module  MOD1  and MOD2 but not their children for being marked
                as flexModels:

                set_proto_mode -identify_exclude_module {MOD1 MOD2}

              * The following command sets the prototyping  model  to  exclude
                the  modules MOD3 and MOD4 and their children for being marked
                as flexModels:

                set_proto_mode -identify_exclude_module_tree {MOD3 MOD4}

              * The following command specifies the the  estimated  delay  per
                micron  for the routing layer Metal1 as 0.50, Metal2 to Metal5
                as 0.25, and Metal6 to Metal7 as 0.14:

                set_proto_mode     -timing_ps_per_micron     {Metal1      0.50
                Metal2:Metal5 0.25 Metal6:Metal7 0.14}

              * The following command specifies the estimated delay per micron
                values that will be used for all timing views:

                set_proto_mode  -timing_ps_per_micron  {M1  0.90 Metal2:Metal4
                0.50 Metal5:Metal6 0.25}

              * The following command specifies the estimated layer pair value
                for specific views:

                set_proto_mode  -timing_ps_per_micron  {setup_func  {M1   0.90
                Metal2:Metal4  0.50 Metal5:Metal6 0.25} hold_func {Metal1 0.60
                Metal2:Metal4 0.30 Metal5:Metal6 0.15}}

              *

                The specified percentage of flexModels will be used to charac-
                terized for flexFiller routing blockage is 30%.

                set_proto_mode -create_characterize_percent_rt_blkg 0.3

              * The following command  specifies  that  instance  group  based
                identify_proto_model   will   keep  user-specified  FlexModels
                Metal1 and Metal2 and identify all others  as  instance  group
                based FlexModels.

                set_proto_model -model Metal1 -type flex_module

                set_proto_model -model Metal2 -type flex_module

                set_proto_mode -identify_algorithm instgroup_based

                identify_proto_model

                report_proto_model -identified

              * The  following command ensures that the hierarchy under hinst1
                is maintained and modules under hinst1 are not be  mixed  with
                other hierarchical modules.

                set_proto_mode -identify_algorithm instgroup_based

                set_proto_mode -identify_honor_objects_hierarchy {hinst1}

                identify_proto_model

Related Information
              *

                get_proto_mode

              * identify_proto_model

              * set_proto_model

              * report_proto_model

              *

                Prototyping Methodologies chapter in the Innovus User Guide

